Before you scrap everything, answer this honestly:
Why do you want to start over?
Is it because:
A) The foundation is broken (Rift concept, power systems, character arcs don't work)
B) You got a BETTER idea that excites you more than current story
C) You're scared/overwhelmed by what you've built (too complex, lost confidence)
D) Specific element is wrong (just Harvest, or everything?)

If A (Foundation Broken):
We fix it. Don't throw away 50+ pages of development. What specifically is broken?
If B (Better Idea):
Tell me the idea first. Let's compare it to current story. Maybe it replaces Harvest but keeps Rei, Isaac, Yuna, the Rift, etc.
If C (Overwhelmed):
Normal feeling. Every writer hits this. Doesn't mean the story is bad—means you're seeing the work ahead. Simplify, don't restart.
If D (Just Harvest):
PERFECT. Keep everything else, replace antagonist faction. That's a tweak, not a rewrite.

