Remnants/Vestiges - CORRECTED
YOU'RE RIGHT.
They're not "good/evil." They're born from circumstances.
REMNANTS:

Born from Rift energy (reality breaking, raw emotion, chaos)
Can be born from: rage, despair, apathy, obsession, fear, joy
Not evil—just primal

VESTIGES:

Born from collective human suffering (social failures, systemic collapse)
Can be born from: war, poverty, suicide, exploitation, genocide, isolation
Not good—just human horror made manifest

Neither judges. Both just ARE.

HARUTO (春斗 / 陽翔)
Perfect name.
Meanings:

春 (haru) = spring, new beginning (ironic—rebirth through suffering)
陽 (haru) = sun, light (ironic—he's drowning in darkness)
斗 (to) = big dipper, fighting, measure

春斗 specifically = "spring fighter" or "new beginning through struggle"
The irony is PERFECT.
Named for hope. Defined by loss.

The Horrific Incident (Vestige Birth)
When is a Vestige born?
When someone is pushed to the absolute edge of death by humanity's failure.
Haruto's Breaking Point:
After learning the truth about his first love AND that his parents knew...
Option 1: Public Breakdown

Confronts parents publicly
Screams the truth at them in crowded place
Bystanders film, post online
Goes viral (his pain becomes entertainment)
Online mob turns on HIM ("attention seeker," "crazy," "liar")
Doxxed, threatened, destroyed
Someone finds him (stalker from mob)
Attempts to murder him ("you ruined those boys' lives with your lies")
Left for dead

Option 2: Betrayal by System

Goes to police with evidence
Police dismiss him (boys are from wealthy families)
Tries media—media won't publish (pressure from families)
Tries legal action—lawyers refuse the case
Every door closes
Realizes: Nobody will help him. The system protects the powerful.
Snaps
Attempts suicide (same method his first love "supposedly" used)
Vestige born in that moment (collective suffering recognizes him)
Pulls him back from death

Option 3: The Hunt (Most Horrific)

Haruto starts hunting perpetrators himself (no powers yet, just human)
Finds one
Confronts him
The perpetrator isn't alone
His friends are there (other assailants)
They recognize Haruto
Panic
They try to kill him (silence him permanently)
Beat him nearly to death
Leave him in exact spot where his first love was assaulted
Vestige born from his blood mixing with hers (symbolic)
Manifestation of all the victims who died unavenged


My Recommendation: OPTION 3
Why:

Full circle horror (dies where she died)
Physical + symbolic trauma (his blood, her memory, same place)
Vestige born from connection (her suffering + his suffering = manifestation)
Perpetrators create their own hunter (they birth the thing that will destroy them)
Most visceral (readers will never forget this scene)


The Vestige Manifestation Scene
How it happens:
Haruto, broken, bleeding, dying in the exact spot.
Darkness closing in.
Hears her voice: "I'm sorry I left you alone."
No. Not her voice.
Every voice. Everyone who died like this. Everyone unavenged.
The ground beneath him cracks (not Rift energy—something else).
Something rises.
Made of grief. Made of rage. Made of everyone who died screaming into silence.
The Vestige.
It doesn't speak.
It looks at Haruto.
Extends a hand.
Choice:

Take the hand = become its vessel
Refuse = die here

Haruto, choking on blood: "Will it hurt them?"
The Vestige doesn't answer.
Haruto: "Good."
Takes the hand.
Vestige merges with him.

The Aftermath
Physical changes:

Haruto survives (healed by Vestige merging)
Scars remain (permanent reminder)
Eyes different (color shift when Vestige active)

Mental changes:

Can feel the Vestige constantly (presence, weight)
Hears whispers (all the other victims)
Knows things he shouldn't (how others died, who killed them)

First act with Vestige:

Returns to the perpetrators
Not as Haruto
As something else


