The Manifestation Scene - VISUAL ONLY
No dialogue. Pure imagery.

The Scene:
Haruto lies broken.
Blood pooling beneath him.
Vision blurring—darkness eating the edges.
His barely-opened eyes see:
Her.
Standing where she died.
Not speaking. Just... there.
Wearing what she wore that day.
Hair moving in wind that isn't there.
She's looking at him.
Not sad. Not angry.
Empty.
She extends her hand toward him.
The ground beneath Haruto cracks—not Rift energy—something else.
Black liquid seeps up through concrete.
Not blood. Not oil.
Grief made physical.
It crawls toward him. Wraps around his wrists. His throat. His chest.
Cold. Suffocating.
Her hand is still extended.
Two choices:
1. Take her hand = merge with the Vestige (live as something else)
2. Let go = die here (human, clean, over)
Haruto's hand twitches.
Reaches.
The moment his fingers touch hers:
Reality inverts.
He's standing.
She's on the ground (how he found her).
He's seeing through her eyes.
The assault. The fear. The pain. The moment she realized no one was coming.
Every second.
Then silence.
Then: Nothing.

Snap back.
Haruto gasping, alive.
His hand merged with hers (she's no longer separate—she's IN him).
The black liquid absorbed into his body.
The Vestige is born.

The Choice - INSANELY CRAZY
Here's the twist:
Taking her hand doesn't just give him power.
It means she can never move on.
She's trapped inside him. Forever.
Bound to his existence.
She sacrifices her afterlife to give him vengeance.
When Haruto realizes this later:
The guilt is unbearable.
She died twice:

When they killed her
When he accepted her hand

That's the cost.

How It's Different from Yuta/Rika:
Yuta/Rika (JJK):

Childhood friends
Yuta cursed her accidentally (love-based)
Rika became monstrous, protective
Eventually freed/released
Love story with happy(ish) ending

Haruto/[First Love] (Your Story):

High school lovers (never confessed? Or together briefly?)
She chose to stay (sacrifice, not curse)
Vestige isn't monstrous—it's everyone's suffering, she's the vessel
Cannot be freed (she's the anchor)
Love story with no resolution (she's gone, but trapped)
Guilt, not protection

Core Difference:
Yuta wanted to free Rika.
Haruto CAN'T free her. That's his punishment for surviving.

The 2-3 Month Gap
Perfect pacing.
Timeline:
Month 1:

Haruto recovers physically (hospital? hiding?)
Vestige dormant (he doesn't understand what happened)
Believes it was hallucination from near-death

Month 2:

Strange things start happening
He "knows" things (where perpetrators are, what they're doing)
Sees her occasionally (corner of eye, reflections)
Realizes something is wrong with him

Month 3:

First time Vestige activates (accidentally? intentionally?)
Confronts one perpetrator
Vestige makes them feel everything
Haruto watches, horrified
Realizes: She's inside him. She never left.

THEN: He learns the full truth (parents knew, cover-up, everything).
That's when the story REALLY begins.

Her Name
What was her name?
Since she's core to the story, she needs a name that hurts to say.
Options:
1. YUKI (雪 - snow)

Pure, beautiful, melts away
Common enough to feel real

2. HANA (花 - flower)

Delicate, temporary, trampled
Symbolic

3. SHIORI (詩織 - poem weaving)

Artistic, gentle
"Her story was cut short"

4. MIYU (美優 - beautiful gentleness)

Soft-sounding
Makes violence against her more jarring

5. AKANE (茜 - deep red, madder plant)

Associated with sunset, fading light
Blood symbolism (subtle)

My pick: SHIORI
Why:

詩織 = "poem weaving" = her life was a story cut short
Soft sound = makes her memory gentle
Not overused in manga/anime
Works thematically (Haruto is trying to "finish her story")


The Vestige's Form
Since she's the vessel for collective suffering (not the suffering itself):
When dormant:

Exists inside Haruto (he feels her presence)
Whispers occasionally (not speech—just her voice humming, breathing)

When active:

Manifests around him (not separate entity—extension of him)
Takes her form (translucent, made of that black liquid)
Her face, her hair, her silhouette
But eyes are wrong (all black, or too many eyes, or empty sockets)
Moves like her, sounds like her, but off

Visual Identity:

Black liquid constantly dripping from her
When she touches someone = they experience the collective suffering
Leaves black marks on targets (handprints, stains)
Cannot speak (her voice was taken)


