The Manifestation Scene - REVISED
What Actually Happens:
Haruto lies broken, beaten, dying.
Blood beneath him. Vision fading.
His barely-opened eyes see her standing there.
She extends her hand.
He closes his eyes.
Accepts death. Or her. Doesn't matter anymore.

When he opens them:
He's not at the assault site.
He's somewhere else.
The place they always planned to visit.
(You choose where—beach? Mountain viewpoint? Specific location in Japan?)
Standing. Uninjured. Clean.
Sunset (or dawn—liminal time).
She's there.
Twenty meters away. Back turned. Looking at the view.
Haruto's hand moves to his jacket pocket (instinct).
Feels something.
Pulls it out.
The ring.
The one he bought but never gave her.
Simple silver band. Nothing fancy.
He stares at it.
Looks up.
She's still there. Not moving.
He walks toward her.

As he gets closer:
He sees her properly now.
What does she look like?

SHIORI'S VESTIGE FORM
Visual Options:
OPTION 1: Almost Human (Heartbreaking)
Appearance:

Looks exactly as she did when alive
Same hair, same uniform/clothes, same face
But eyes are different:

Glowing faintly (not bright—soft, sad glow)
Color shifted (normal brown → pale gold/silver)
When emotional, light intensifies


Skin slightly translucent in certain light
Doesn't cast shadow

Why this works:

Most painful option (she looks REAL but isn't)
-Haruto can almost believe she's alive
The small differences are subtle horror


OPTION 2: Ethereal/Fading (Tragic)
Appearance:

Looks like her but slightly transparent
Edges blur softly (like watercolor painting)
Hair moves even when there's no wind
When she moves, brief after-image trails
Can partially phase through objects (unintentionally)
Solid to Haruto's touch, intangible to others

Why this works:

Visually distinct from human
"She's here but not here" made literal
Can't fully return (permanent loss emphasized)


OPTION 3: Marked by Death (Disturbing)
Appearance:

Looks exactly like her
BUT: Visible marks from how she died

Bruises fading in/out
Clothing torn where it was torn
Sometimes reverts to "that moment"


She can't fully control it
When calm: looks normal
When emotional: death resurfaces visually

Why this works:

Constant reminder of what happened
Horror of "she can never escape that moment"
Most traumatic for Haruto (he sees her death constantly)


OPTION 4: Idealized Memory (Bittersweet)
Appearance:

Looks like Haruto's memory of her (not reality)
Slightly more beautiful than she was (memory bias)
Frozen at her happiest moment with him
Never ages, never changes
Always smiling softly (even when sad)

Why this works:

She's his memory made real (not truly her)
He can never know if it's really her or his idealization
Question: Is this Shiori, or Haruto's grief given form?


MY RECOMMENDATION: OPTION 1 (Almost Human)
Why:

Most emotionally devastating
She looks SO real that it hurts
Subtle wrongness (eyes, no shadow) = constant reminder
Maximizes pain when he realizes she's truly gone


SHIORI'S FULL DESCRIPTION (Option 1 Applied)
Physical:

Height: 160cm (slightly shorter than Haruto)
Build: Slender, delicate
Hair: Black, straight, shoulder-length (how she wore it)
Face: Soft features, gentle expression
Clothing: School uniform (what she died in? Or last happy memory outfit?)

Vestige Traits:

Eyes: Pale silver-gold glow (soft, not bright)
Skin: Slightly translucent in direct light
No shadow cast
Doesn't need to breathe (chest doesn't rise/fall)
Warm to Haruto's touch (not cold/dead)
Can't eat, drink, sleep (doesn't need to)

Behavioral:

Moves naturally (not stiff or ghostly)
Expressions genuine (she's still "her")
Can touch physical objects
Voice sounds exactly like she did
But can't feel physical sensations (no pain, no pleasure, no temperature)


The Conversation
Haruto approaches. Stops a few steps away.
The Dialogue:
Haruto: (voice breaking) "...Shiori?"
Shiori: (turns slowly, smiles sadly) "Hi, Haruto."
Haruto: (tears falling, doesn't realize) "You're... how are you...?"
Shiori: "I'm not. I'm not here. Not really."
Haruto: "Then what—"
Shiori: "You were dying. I couldn't let you die alone."
(Pause. He steps closer.)
Haruto: "I'm sorry. I'm so sorry. I didn't know—I should have—"
Shiori: (gently) "You couldn't have known. Nobody could."
Haruto: "They said you... they told me you—"
Shiori: "I know what they told you. It wasn't true."
(Haruto's hands shake. The ring slips slightly in his grip.)
Shiori: (notices the ring) "You kept it."
Haruto: "I was going to—I wanted to—"
Shiori: "I know."
(Long silence. Just wind, sunset, two people who can't be together.)
Haruto: "What happened to you?"
Shiori: "...Do you really want to know?"
Haruto: (barely breathing) "Yes."
Shiori: (looks away) "They hurt me. It lasted hours. I screamed. Nobody came."
(Haruto's knees nearly give out.)
Shiori: "When it was over, they left me. I was still alive. For a while."
Haruto: "I'll kill them. I'll—"
Shiori: (firm) "Haruto. Listen to me."
(He stops.)
Shiori: "You're not dead. But you're not alive the way you were. Something happened when you touched my hand."
Haruto: "What did you do to me?"
Shiori: "I gave you a choice. You chose."
Haruto: "I don't understand—"
Shiori: "I'm a Vestige now. Born from... what they did. From how I died. From how much I—" (stops herself) "—from everything I felt."
Haruto: "What's a Vestige?"
Shiori: "When someone dies with overwhelming emotion—rage, despair, love, betrayal—and that emotion is strong enough... sometimes it doesn't disappear. Sometimes it takes form."
(She looks at her hands.)
Shiori: "I'm not Shiori anymore. Not completely. I'm what she felt. What she wanted. What she couldn't do."
Haruto: "And now you're... with me?"
Shiori: "Bonded. We're connected. I exist through you now."
Haruto: (realizes) "So you can never—"
Shiori: "No. I can't move on. I can't rest. As long as you live, I exist."
(Haruto's face breaks.)
Haruto: "I trapped you."
Shiori: "You saved me. In a way."
Haruto: "How is this saving you?!"
Shiori: (quietly) "Because now I can make them feel it. What they did. Every second."
(Pause. Her eyes glow brighter briefly.)
Shiori: "That's what Vestiges do. We force understanding. We make the living feel what the dead felt."
Haruto: "You want revenge."
Shiori: "I want justice. There's a difference."

The Ring - The Choice
Shiori: (looks at ring in his hand) "You were going to propose."
Haruto: (can't speak)
Shiori: "You still can. If you want."
Haruto: "What?"
Shiori: "The ring. You have two choices."
(She extends her left hand.)
Shiori: "Put it on my finger. Bind us completely. I become part of you—fully. We share everything. Your pain, my power. Inseparable."
(Pause.)
Shiori: "Or keep it. Remember me. But stay separate. I exist near you, but not within you. We're connected, but not merged."

THE CHOICE BREAKDOWN:
OPTION A: Put Ring On Her Finger (Full Bond)
Effects:

Shiori fully merges with Haruto (internal presence)
Can manifest outside him, but usually internal
He can access her memories (sees how she died—TORTURE)
She can access his emotions (feels his guilt constantly)
Stronger power connection (her abilities flow through him naturally)
But: More painful for both (shared suffering)

Symbolism:

Marriage through death
"Till death do us part" inverted (death bound them)
Most romantic but most tragic


OPTION B: Keep the Ring (Partial Bond)
Effects:

Shiori exists beside him (external presence)
Separate consciousness, separate space
He can't access her memories (protected from seeing her death)
She can't feel his emotions directly (less burden on her)
Weaker power connection (must coordinate consciously)
But: Less painful for both (maintained boundaries)

Symbolism:

Respecting her autonomy even in death
Guilt: "I won't force you into this"
Less romantic but more respectful


MY RECOMMENDATION: He chooses OPTION A
Why:

Maximum emotional devastation
He chooses to burden her further (guilt compounds)
Romantic gesture twisted into curse
She accepts (she wants this—to be with him)
Readers' hearts shatter

The Scene:
Haruto: (crying, hands shaking) "I can't... I can't trap you more than I already have—"
Shiori: (steps closer) "You're not trapping me. I'm choosing this."
Haruto: "Why?"
Shiori: "Because I love you. And I'm not done yet."
(She places her hand in his.)
Shiori: "Put it on."
Haruto: (barely able to see through tears) "Shiori..."
Shiori: (smiling, crying—can Vestiges cry? Yes, now) "It's okay. I want this."
(He slides the ring onto her finger.)
(The moment it's on: Reality shifts.)

What Happens After Ring Goes On:
Visual:

Her form glows intensely (brief, blinding)
She dissolves into light
Light flows into Haruto's chest (heart area)
He gasps, falls to knees
Hears her voice inside his mind: "I'm here. I'm with you."

Return to Reality:

He's back at the assault site
Alive, healed (mostly—scars remain)
Ring on his own finger now (not hers—merged)
Alone
But not alone


