OPTION 1: SHIRAKAWA-GO (白川郷) - Traditional Village

UNESCO World Heritage site
Gassho-style farmhouses (thatched roofs)
Mountains surrounding, incredibly peaceful
Snow in winter (pure white, isolated feeling)
They planned to visit during winter, see it together
Symbolism: Traditional, timeless—everything they'll never have

OPTION 2: LAKE KAWAGUCHI (河口湖) - Mt. Fuji View

One of Fuji Five Lakes
Perfect reflection of Mt. Fuji on still water
Cherry blossoms in spring OR autumn colors
Benches along lakeside (place to sit, talk quietly)
They wanted to see sunrise here together
Symbolism: Reflection, duality, beauty that fades

OPTION 3: HITACHI SEASIDE PARK (ひたち海浜公園) - Flower Fields

Nemophila (baby blue eyes flowers) covering hills
Looks like ocean of blue flowers meeting sky
Or kochia (red bushes) in autumn
Endless, peaceful, overwhelming beauty
They wanted to take photos here together
Symbolism: Life, growth, things that bloom and die

OPTION 4: FUSHIMI INARI SHRINE - Torii Path (Empty)

Thousands of red torii gates creating tunnel
But deserted (early morning? Wrong season?)
Just endless path, no people
Sacred, liminal space
They planned to walk through together, make wishes
Symbolism: Path to the afterlife, thresholds, crossing over

OPTION 5: JIGOKUDANI (地獄谷) - "Hell Valley"

Volcanic valley, steam rising from ground
Hot springs, sulfur smell, barren landscape
Beautiful but hostile (nature that kills)
Snow monkeys bathe there (life persisting)
They joked about visiting "hell" together ironically
Symbolism: Hell, suffering, survival despite conditions

OPTION 6: TOTTORI SAND DUNES (鳥取砂丘)

Massive sand dunes (only large dunes in Japan)
Looks like desert meeting ocean
Endless, empty, quiet
Sunset turns sand gold/orange
They wanted to see the "desert" in Japan together
Symbolism: Emptiness, time passing, footprints erased


