THE CONVERSATION - REVISED
Haruto walks toward her. She turns.
Shiori: "Hi, Haruto."
Haruto: (voice breaking) "...How?"
Shiori: (looks around) "We're here. We finally made it."
Haruto: "This isn't real. You're not—"
Shiori: "I'm not. But I am. Does that make sense?"
Haruto: (tears falling) "No. None of this—"
Shiori: "You were dying. I pulled you here."
Haruto: "Here?"
Shiori: (gestures to location) "Where we always wanted to go. I thought... if you were going to die, you should die somewhere beautiful."
(Pause. He steps closer, stops.)
Haruto: "I'm sorry."
Shiori: "For what?"
Haruto: "For not knowing. For believing them. For not—"
Shiori: (gently) "You couldn't have known. They lied. Everyone lied."
Haruto: "What happened to you?"
Shiori: (looks away) "Do you really want to know?"
Haruto: "Yes."
Shiori: "...They hurt me. It lasted a long time. I screamed for help. Nobody came. When they were done, they left me there. I was still alive. For a while."
(Haruto's knees buckle. She catches him—solid, warm, real.)
Haruto: "I'll kill them. Every single one—"
Shiori: "Haruto. Look at me."
(He does.)
Shiori: "You're not dead. But you're not the same anymore."
Haruto: "What did you do to me?"
Shiori: "I didn't do anything. You chose. When you took my hand."
Haruto: "I don't understand—"
Shiori: "When someone dies the way I did—with that much emotion, that much pain, that much... unfinished feeling—sometimes we don't disappear completely."
(She looks at her hands.)
Shiori: "We become something else. Not alive. Not gone. Something in between."
Haruto: "What are you?"
Shiori: "I don't know what people call us. But I know what I am. I'm what happens when someone dies screaming and nobody listens."
Haruto: "And now?"
Shiori: "Now I'm bound to you. I exist because you exist. We're connected."
Haruto: (realizes) "You can never rest."
Shiori: "No. As long as you're alive, I'm here."
Haruto: (horrified) "I trapped you."
Shiori: "You gave me a reason to stay."
Haruto: "This isn't—you should be—"
Shiori: "I should be dead. I am. But I'm also here. With you."
(Pause. Wind moves her hair.)
Shiori: "And now... I can make them understand. What they did. Every second of it."
Haruto: "How?"
Shiori: "That's what we do. We make people feel. Really feel. What we felt."

THE RING CHOICE - REVISED (Option B for Now)
Shiori notices the ring in his hand.
Shiori: "You kept it."
Haruto: (can barely look at it) "I was going to... I wanted to ask you..."
Shiori: "I know."
(Long silence.)
Shiori: "You could still put it on me. If you want."
Haruto: "What?"
Shiori: (extends her left hand) "We're together now. In a way. You could make it official."
Haruto: (shaking) "I can't. I can't trap you more than I already have."
Shiori: "You're not—"
Haruto: "You should be free. You should be at peace. Not stuck with me."
Shiori: "Haruto—"
Haruto: (closes his fist around ring) "No. I'll keep this. And one day—when this is over, when they've paid, when it's done—I'll put it where it belongs."
(His voice breaks.)
Haruto: "That's a promise. I'll make this right. I'll make you free."
Shiori: (smiles sadly) "You can't free me. I'm already gone."
Haruto: "Then I'll avenge you."
Shiori: "That's not the same as—"
Haruto: "It's all I have left."
(She looks at him. Reaches out. Touches his face—warm, solid, real.)
Shiori: "Okay. Keep the ring. Keep your promise."
(Pause.)
Shiori: "But Haruto?"
Haruto: "Yeah?"
Shiori: "When this is over... don't forget to live. For both of us."

RETURN TO REALITY
The moment she says that:
Reality shifts.
Location fades (mountains/lake/dunes dissolving).
Haruto back at the assault site.
Alive. Healed (mostly—scars remain).
Alone.
Ring in his pocket.
But her voice in his mind:
"I'm here. I'm with you. Always."
He stands. Looks at his hands.
They're different (eyes? Aura? Something visible?).
Cut to black.

