THIS IS IT.

THE CORE CONCEPT:
HARUTO (Normal State):

Guilty, broken, hesitant
Holds back from violence
Tries to be "good"
Slower, weaker, human

HARUTO + SHIORI MERGED (Active State):

All hesitation gone
All guilt suppressed
Pure rage, sadness, vengeance
Faster, stronger, inhuman
Talks like Sukuna (cruel, honest, mocking)

The Twist:
When Shiori "gives him form," she's not just powering him up.
She's taking over partially.
It's not full possession (he's still conscious).
But her emotions override his.
Her rage becomes his actions.

HOW IT WORKS:
Activation:
Haruto doesn't "transform" like typical shonen.
Shiori emerges from him.
Not separate—overlapping.
Visual:

Her form appears behind/around him (translucent)
Her hands overlap his hands
Her eyes overlap his eyes (his eyes glow her color)
When he moves, she moves with him (like puppet and puppeteer)
Two bodies, one motion

Or:
Her form wraps around him like armor/aura.

Not solid armor—flowing, shifting
Made of emotional energy (not physical)
Looks like he's being embraced from behind by a ghost

Effect:

Speed increases drastically (she's not bound by living body limits)
Strength increases (emotional energy enhances physical)
Perception changes (sees things differently—weak points, fears, guilt)
Personality shift (her emotions dominate)


THE PERSONALITY SHIFT (Sukuna-Style)
Normal Haruto:

"I'm sorry."
"I have to do this."
"Please, just tell me what happened."

Haruto + Shiori Active:

"Beg louder. I want to hear it."
"You're already dead. You just don't know it yet."
"She begged too. Did you listen?"

The Voice:
When active, does he sound like:
Option A: His voice, but colder/sharper (subtle shift)
Option B: Dual voice (his + hers layered, echoing)
Option C: Her voice speaks through him occasionally (she interjects mid-sentence)
My Pick: OPTION C
Example:
Perpetrator: "Please, I didn't—"
Haruto: "You did. I know you did—"
Shiori's voice (through his mouth, different tone): "—because I was there. I felt it. Every. Second."
Perpetrator: (realization, horror)
Haruto: (back to his voice) "And now you will too."
The Horror:

Perpetrator realizes: She's inside him
They're not fighting one person—they're fighting the victim they killed
The dead girl is hunting them


WHAT CAN THEY DO? (ABILITIES)
