OPTION C: Interjection (Her Voice Breaks Through)
As Haruto uses form more, Shiori's presence strengthens.
Sometimes she speaks instead of him mid-sentence.
Example:
Haruto: "You don't deserve—"
Shiori (her voice suddenly, through his mouth): "—mercy. He was going to say mercy. But I'm not him."
Perpetrator: (realization, horror)
Haruto (his voice, surprised): "Shiori—"
Shiori: "They don't get to forget. I didn't get to forget."
Back to Haruto: "...No. They don't."
Effect:

Shows they're merging (boundaries blurring)
Haruto sometimes surprised by what comes out
Shiori's consciousness growing stronger


Late Story (When Bond Deepens):
OPTION A: His Voice, But Changed
Eventually, Haruto's voice in form sounds like his own.
But:

Colder (no warmth, no hesitation)
Sharper (every word cuts)
Cruel honesty (says things he'd never say normally)

This is worse than dual voice.
Because it means: He's internalized her.
Not two people speaking.
One person who's both.
Example:
Perpetrator: "Please, I have a family—"
Haruto (cold, casual): "So did she. Parents who'll never see her again. A brother who found her. A boyfriend who couldn't save her."
(Perfect calm, devastating truth)
Perpetrator: "I didn't mean—"
Haruto: "Yes, you did. You just didn't think it mattered."

SUKUNA-STYLE DIALOGUE (ELEVATED)
You said:

"I WANNA MAKE IT BETTER"
"WHOEVER READS IT MUST FEEL THE WEIGHT"

Here's how we elevate beyond Sukuna:
Sukuna's Style:

Arrogant, mocking, entertained by suffering
Views humans as insects
Cruel for cruelty's sake
"You're boring me."

Haruto/Shiori's Style:

Painfully honest, not arrogant
Emotionally devastating, not just physical
Forces self-awareness, not just fear
Personal, not general cruelty


EXAMPLES:
Instead of Sukuna's:

"You're weak. Pathetic."

Haruto/Shiori says:

"You had a choice. She didn't. And you chose this."

(Not about strength—about moral failure)

Instead of Sukuna's:

"Die."

Haruto/Shiori says:

"Live. And remember this feeling. Every day. For the rest of your life."

(Worse than death—psychological warfare)

When Perpetrator Begs:
Perpetrator: "I was just following them! I didn't start it!"
Haruto/Shiori: "Neither did she. But when she begged, did you stop? Did you say 'I'm just following'?"
(Turns their defense into condemnation)

When Perpetrator Cries:
Perpetrator: (sobbing) "I'm sorry—"
Haruto/Shiori: "You're crying. Good. She cried too. For hours. Nobody listened. Why should I listen to you?"
(Mirrors their cruelty back at them)

When Perpetrator Tries to Run:
Haruto/Shiori: (casual, not shouting) "Run. She ran too. See how far you get."
(Calm certainty—they're already caught)

After Using Empathy Attack:
Perpetrator: (on ground, broken) "What did you do to me—"
Haruto/Shiori: (crouching beside them) "Nothing. I just showed you what already happened. The past. Your past."
(Not magic—just truth)

THE WEIGHT FACTOR
What makes readers FEEL the weight:

Haruto isn't enjoying this (even when Shiori's emotions dominate, there's sadness underneath)
Every line references Shiori's suffering (constant reminder of what was lost)
Perpetrators realize they're facing their victim (psychological horror)
Dialogue is SPECIFIC (not generic threats—personal details)
Calm delivery (scarier than screaming—implies certainty)


